author: CNN
description:
More than 1,000 demonstrations against the Trump administration’s immigration crackdown are planned across the country this weekend as outrage spreads over the fatal shooting of a Minnesota woman by an ICE agent on Wednesday. A large crowd has gathered at a Minneapolis city park for a rally and march this afternoon, after hundreds of people attended a protest downtown yesterday.

CNN's Omar Jimenez reports from protests near Minneapolis, and Camila DeChalus reports from a protest outside the White House.

3:45 Minneapolis mayor statement
8:00 Nationwide protests
8:22 Reporting from White House protest 

#ICEShooting #Protests #News
title: Protests in Minneapolis, nationwide after deadly ICE shooting

description: Danish MP Rasmus Jarlov talks with CNN’s Jim Sciutto and reacts to President Donald Trump’s comments on Greenland that if he is unable to make a deal to acquire the territory “the easy way,” then he will have to “do it the hard way.”
title: Danish MP: Greenlanders ‘don’t want to become Americanized’

author: CNN
description: The tranquility of Greenland's wilderness lies in stark contrast to Trump's latest threats for the US to acquire the country. While many Greenlanders are staunchly opposed to such a takeover, others worry that there's nothing Greenland can do if the US is intent on its acquisition. CNN's Nic Robertson reports.
title: How Greenland’s tranquility contrasts with latest Trump threat

author: CNN
description:
At least 65 people have been killed and more than 2,300 arrested in two weeks of anti-government protests that have rocked Iran, the US-based Human Rights Activists News Agency said. The 
demonstrations have taken place in a wave of nationwide unrest over crippling economic conditions. 

An internet blackout across the country imposed by the authorities is also ongoing, according to a watchdog. Authorities had cut internet access and telephone lines in Tehran and other cities on Thursday.

President Donald Trump has threatened to attack Iran if security forces respond with force and Secretary of State Marco Rubio said the US supports the country’s people. Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei urged Trump to “focus on his own country” and blamed the US for inciting the protests.

CNN correspondent Paula Hancocks reports from Abu Dhabi, and Fareed Zakaria speaks with Kaitlan Collins.

0:20 Protests in Tehran
0:53 CNN correspondent reports
1:35 Pr
title: Deadly protests erupt in Iran
